    /src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-gridfs-bucket.c, line: 382
    {color:red}Calling "bson_iter_init" without checking return value (as is done elsewhere 144 out of 177 times).{color} 
{code:first-line=382}
       bson_iter_init (&iter, &file_doc);
{code}

To reproduce:
{code:c}
bson_t test = BSON_INITIALIZER;
bson_append_date_time (&test, "a", -1, 1356351330001);
printf("%s\n", bson_as_relaxed_extended_json (&test, NULL));
{code}
Prints:
{noformat}
{ "a" : { "$date" : "2012-12-24T12:15:30.  1Z" } }
{noformat}
Which uses spaces in the millisecond portion instead of zeroes.

